  <bioghist id="aspace_9d9065fdd617d237d719ba40f87a34b0">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Professor of Botany at Wisconsin, Washington, and Illinois Universities, 1883-1912; and director, Missouri Botanical Gardens, 1889-1912.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_c6ec9285c2714c7fd2ad7ab8d055079f">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>General incoming personal and professional correspondence, c. 1879-c. 1845; correspondence, clippings, and other items concerning his work in the Missouri Botanical Gardens, his monographs, the naming of Mount Trelease, Colorado, activities of the Society of American Bacteriologists, and other subjects; and photographs and miscellaneous printed matter. Also Trelease's correspondence, deeds, and drawings concerning family cemetery plots in Urbana, Illinois, and St. Louis Missouri.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_5d9e648d1521003fa76fda51b213042c">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>William Trelease papers, #2560. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
